result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler Lee Kuhn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tyler Lee Kuhn is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tyler Lee Kuhn was found guilty of 4th Degree Sexual Assault [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3m).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Matthew L Hartung, DF ATTY: Alex Andrea & DF:  Tyler Lee Kuhn appeared from jail.  Court called at 9:05 a.m.  Includes case 15CF302, 15CF443, 15CF538, 15CF576, 15CF578, 15CM491 & 15TR1210.  Set for Plea/Sentencing.  Attorneys recite the agreement.  State files a 3 year DJOC for 15CF538.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalties for 15CF578.  DE pleads Guilty to Ct 1,  Ct. 3 & Ct. 7 in 15CF578.  Crt uses the testimony at the preliminary hearing and the police reports to accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE adjudicated guilty of Ct 1, Ct. 3 & Ct. 7 in 15CF578. On motion of the State, Crt reads in for restitution purposes and dismisses Ct 2, 4-6 & Ct. 8-11  & Ct. 12-22 in 15CF578. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:   

Ct. 1, Ct. 3 & Ct. 7 to run concurrent with the DJOC

S/W 3 years probation with conditions
   Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
-   It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons by the DA's office (list will be provided to the DE) and Joe Maser.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  
- AODA and follow through with any recommended treatment,  therapy or a psychological examination
- DE to undergo a psychological examination and follow through with any recommended therapy or treatment
- Apology letters to all victims within 30 days from todays hearing 
- 75 hours of community service
- DE to attend MRT
- DE to attend a victim empathy panel
- DE to seek and maintain fulltime employment
- DE to sign up for probation on the day he is released from jail
- All bonds to remain in effect until the DE reports to probation and then bond 15CF538 will then be the bond of record
- DE to submit to a DNA sample before being released fromt he jail
- Court costs for Ct. 1 $268.00 and $250 for DNA surcharge to be paid through the DOC
- Court costs of Ct. 3 $243.00 and $200 for DNA surcharge to be paid through the DOC
- Court costs of Ct. 7 $243.00 and $200 for the DNA surcharge to be paid through the DOC
- Restitution joint and several with Joes Maser in the amount of $6,512 to be paid before the court costs and through the DOC
- DE is eligible and can apply for expungment upon full completion of the DJOC and probation  in 15CF578 Ct. 1 only


Court proceeds with 15CF302.  State moves to amend Ct. 1 to 940.225(3m) 4th degree sexual assault.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads Guilty to the amended Ct 1 15CF302.  Crt reviews the police reports.  Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds the DE adjudicated guilty of the amended Ct 1 in 15CF302. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 2 & Ct 3 & 15CF576, 15CF443 & 15CM491. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:

Ct. 1 in 15CF302
- DE sentenced to 120 days in the St. Croix County jail 
- Credit for 90 days served
- Court costs of $243.00 and $200 for the DNA surcharge to be paid through the DOC

Court proceeds with 15CF538.  State files a 3 year DJOC for Ct. 3.   On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct. 1-2 and Ct 4-6.  Crt reviews the police report.  Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and stays the adjudication of guilt pending full performance of the DJOC.  Court questions the DE.  Court agrees to the DJOC and signs the order
